h3. Summary

The dropdown to assign permissions to a comment becomes detatched from its root when scrolling.
h3. Environment
 * JIRA 7.2.3;
 * Chrome 53.0.2785.143;
 * OSX 10.11.2.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Go to the View Issue page for any issue which you have permission to comment on;
 # Being editing a new comment. Your screen must be short enough that accessing the "Comment" button requires vertical scroll. If your screen is too large, add some filler text to the description to grow the page height;
 # Click on the padlock icon below the edit box to open the permissions dialog (don't select a permission level or close the dialog);
 # With the dialog still open, scroll back to the top of the page.

h3. Expected Results

The comment permissions dialog closes, or stays attached to its root as the page scrolls.
h3. Actual Results

The dialog becomes detatched and scrolls up with the page, floating over other elements.
h3.

