h3. Problem Definition

If either the project lead or the component lead do not possess permissions to assign issue, they will show up normally on the project administration pages. Back on JIRA 4, if either of them were unassignable, the name would show up in red. 
{quote}
As part of my administrative duties, I was using this color-coding to quickly determine if I needed to reach out to the project owner and ask the person to update their project lead or component lead. This was a proactive measure instead of a reactive measure for the customer to complain to me that the user was unassignable. We have 80+ projects, and, on a daily basis, I am removing terminated employees from groups. It was a quick and easy check for me. Please consider putting back the color-coding.
{quote}

h3. Suggested Solution
 
Have a visual cue (either a different color or a warning icon) indicating that the user cannot assign issues.

